{"action": "input", "code": "def get_height_width(image: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = image.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(1, w + 1):\n        output_grid[1][j] = output_grid[2][j]\n        output_grid[h][j] = output_grid[h - 1][j]\n    for i in range(1, h + 1):\n        output_grid[i][1] = output_grid[i][2]\n        output_grid[i][w] = output_grid[i][w - 1]\n    return output_grid\ndef overlay_input_grid(output_grid: np.ndarray, input_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid[1:h + 1, 1:w + 1] = input_grid[0:h, 0:w]\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h, w = get_height_width(input_grid)\n    output_grid = create_black_image(h, w)\n    output_grid = overlay_input_grid(output_grid, input_grid, h, w)\n    output_grid = border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid, h, w)\n    return output_grid\ndef create_black_image(h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((h + 2, w + 2), dtype=np.uint8)\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Task description: You are given an image matrix as input. Your task is to perform the following steps:\n\n    # Step 1\n    (h, w) = `Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w respectively.`(input_grid)\n\n    # Step 2\n    output_grid = `Create a new black image matrix of size (h+2) x (w+2), denoted as output_grid.`(h,w)\n\n    # Step 3\n    output_grid = `Overlay the input_grid onto the output_grid in an h*w sized area with (1,1) as the top left corner and (h,w) as the bottom right corner.`(output_grid,input_grid,h,w)\n\n    # Step 4\n    output_grid = `(4-1) Traverse the first row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i+1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-2) Traverse the last row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i-1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-3) Traverse the first column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j+1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-4) Traverse the last column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j-1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid.`(output_grid,h,w)\n\n    return output_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def get_height_width(image: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = image.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(1, w + 1):\n        output_grid[1][j] = output_grid[2][j]\n        output_grid[h][j] = output_grid[h - 1][j]\n    for i in range(1, h + 1):\n        output_grid[i][1] = output_grid[i][2]\n        output_grid[i][w] = output_grid[i][w - 1]\n    return output_grid\ndef overlay_input_grid(output_grid: np.ndarray, input_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid[1:h + 1, 1:w + 1] = input_grid[0:h, 0:w]\n    return output_grid\ndef create_black_image(h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((h + 2, w + 2), dtype=np.uint8)\n    return output_grid", "holes": {"get_height_width": "Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w respectively.", "border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels": "(4-1) Traverse the first row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i+1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-2) Traverse the last row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i-1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-3) Traverse the first column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j+1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-4) Traverse the last column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j-1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid.", "overlay_input_grid": "Overlay the input_grid onto the output_grid in an h*w sized area with (1,1) as the top left corner and (h,w) as the bottom right corner.", "create_black_image": "Create a new black image matrix of size (h+2) x (w+2), denoted as output_grid."}}
{"action": "edit", "code": "def get_height_width(image: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = image.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(1, w + 1):\n        output_grid[0][j] = output_grid[1][j]\n        output_grid[h + 1][j] = output_grid[h][j]\n    for i in range(1, h + 1):\n        output_grid[i][0] = output_grid[i][1]\n        output_grid[i][w + 1] = output_grid[i][w]\n    return output_grid\ndef overlay_input_grid(output_grid: np.ndarray, input_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid[1:h + 1, 1:w + 1] = input_grid[0:h, 0:w]\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    h, w = get_height_width(input_grid)\n    output_grid = create_black_image(h, w)\n    output_grid = overlay_input_grid(output_grid, input_grid, h, w)\n    output_grid = border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid, h, w)\n    return output_grid\ndef create_black_image(h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((h + 2, w + 2), dtype=np.uint8)\n    return output_grid", "user_code": "def border_pixels_to_adjacent_pixels(output_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    for j in range(1, w+1):\n        output_grid[0][j] = output_grid[1][j]\n        output_grid[h+1][j] = output_grid[h][j]\n    for i in range(1, h+1):\n        output_grid[i][0] = output_grid[i][1]\n        output_grid[i][w+1] = output_grid[i][w]\n    return output_grid\n    \ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    # Task description: You are given an image matrix as input. Your task is to perform the following steps:\n\n    # Step 1\n    (h, w) = `Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w respectively.`(input_grid)\n\n    # Step 2\n    output_grid = `Create a new black image matrix of size (h+2) x (w+2), denoted as output_grid.`(h,w)\n\n    # Step 3\n    output_grid = `Overlay the input_grid onto the output_grid in an h*w sized area with (1,1) as the top left corner and (h,w) as the bottom right corner.`(output_grid,input_grid,h,w)\n\n    # Step 4\n    output_grid = `(4-1) Traverse the first row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i+1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-2) Traverse the last row of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i-1,j) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-3) Traverse the first column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j+1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid. (4-4) Traverse the last column of the image matrix and perform the following operations for each pixel at coordinate (i,j): assign the color of pixel (i,j-1) to the current pixel (at coordinate (i,j)) in output_grid.`(output_grid,h,w)\n\n    return output_grid\n    ", "gpt_code": "def get_height_width(image: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    h, w = image.shape[:2]\n    return (h, w)\ndef overlay_input_grid(output_grid: np.ndarray, input_grid: np.ndarray, h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid[1:h + 1, 1:w + 1] = input_grid[0:h, 0:w]\n    return output_grid\ndef create_black_image(h: int, w: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = np.zeros((h + 2, w + 2), dtype=np.uint8)\n    return output_grid", "holes": {"get_height_width": "Get the height and width of the image matrix, denoted as h and w respectively.", "overlay_input_grid": "Overlay the input_grid onto the output_grid in an h*w sized area with (1,1) as the top left corner and (h,w) as the bottom right corner.", "create_black_image": "Create a new black image matrix of size (h+2) x (w+2), denoted as output_grid."}}
